@0    = ~The Underdark... What a perfect place for our reunion, Dusk!~
@1    = ~A bit ambiguous, my lady. However, I won't turn a deaf ear to what you've said.~
@2    = ~"Once there was a brave knight,
though he dreamed of peace, his demeanor was severe.
Then one day he met the love of his life:
an elf with golden hair who became his wife.
She accompanied him in his quest for peace,
and his stern countenance became a mask, at ease,
for love blinded him like a fool,
unaware of the tragedy that would befall him soon..."~
@3    = ~Are you talking to me? How do you know that?! Explain yourself!~
@4    = ~Greetings, my lord. I am Madame Nin, and I am here to ensure your company is pleasurable. Are you interested?~
@5    = ~No, gratitude. <CHARNAME>, we should find a solution to this. Clearly, these people are being forced to work here against their will.~
@6    = ~So... do you desire company for tonight?~
@7    = ~Damn it, stop bothering us, lady.~
@8    = ~No, Yoshimo... no... how could you sell your soul to this wretched being? Damn you, Yoshimo... damn you...~
@9    = ~Are you well? You were unconscious for a while.~
@10   = ~I'm fine, don't worry.~
@11   = ~My body feels strange, as if I'm not in complete control...~

@13   = ~So be it, but don't hesitate to turn to your friends if you need to. We must stick together if we want to get out of here alive.~
@14   = ~It's highly possible that the wizard cast something permanent on you... or perhaps took something away. Thinking about souls sends shivers down my spine, but if yours was taken, we'll get it back. It's a promise, <CHARNAME>.~
@15   = ~What the hell was that? You turned into a bloodthirsty creature, completely insane and out of your senses. <CHARNAME>, that was the avatar of the Slayer, wasn't it? It was both impressive... and chilling at the same time.~
@16   = ~I wouldn't feel very comfortable with so many (especially insane) mages around me. But I believe they have as many reasons as we do to confront Irenicus, <CHARNAME>. Do what you think is right.~
@17   = ~Dusk, the brave warrior. His gaze is severe and determined. You know he wouldn't hesitate to die for his ideals or his comrades.~
@18   = ~Dusk, this isn't your fight. You don't have to follow me.~
@19   = ~You've done a lot for me, Dusk. You can go home if you want to.~
@20   = ~Are you ready to follow me? I need you by my side to win.~
@21   = ~We've come a long way to get here. The only option is to fight, <CHARNAME>. We'll do it together... we'll do it for the fallen!~


@27   = ~We have defeated him! But... something is not right... what's happening?~
@28   = ~A strange vision, <CHARNAME>. Have you brought me to your personal hell? If we make it out of here alive, maybe I'll let you buy me a beer.~
@29   = ~Ever since Waukeen's Promenade, you've left a trail of corpses in your wake, Irenicus... your selfishness and malice have blinded you completely and many innocents have paid for it. But today, we will bring justice for the fallen. Let's go, comrades, to arms!~
@30   = ~Can't sleep? Not surprising. The things that have happened lately... wait, are you well? Your face just went pale all of a sudden.~
@31   = ~Something is happening inside me... Run!~
@32   = ~Dusk, I think I'm transforming again...~
@33   = ~Get out of here, now!~
@34   = ~I... I don't understand... are you trying to tell me something?~ [P_Dusk18]
@35   = ~<CHARNAME>... are you well? This time, I thought you wouldn't return to normal...~
@36   = ~Don't worry... I'm sure we'll find some solution to this... maybe... maybe you should learn to control this power... Although, I don't know if that's advisable. Something tells me you would attract... unwanted attention.~

@37  = ~Stupid elves... we have lived through a torment in the Underdark... only to come across this undeserved mistrust...~

@60   = ~Are they going to burn her alive?... No... just because she's a drow? <CHARNAME>, this is inconceivable. We must do something!~
@61   = ~*whispering* <CHARNAME>, it's clear that we were the ones who broke into their home and killed those vile creatures. Not that I'm complaining, but I smell a rat... We must stay alert.~
@62   = ~Even I can understand that Faldorn is an affront to nature. Using animals for revenge killing is a low and cowardly move. Cernd, I trust you can kick her butt.~
@63   = ~<CHARNAME>, allying ourselves with this creature will mean getting directly involved in an open war against the Shadow Thieves. We must be cautious in our next decisions... the lives of many innocents may be in our hands... If there is a war, I would want to avoid it (although at this point, it seems almost impossible).~


@65   = ~Watch your words, creature. <CHARNAME> may be a nuisance (no offense intended), but at least he speaks clearly, unlike you.~ ~Watch your words, creature. <CHARNAME> may be a nuisance (no offense intended), but at least she speaks clearly, unlike you.~
@66   = ~It seems Irenicus can still be reached. <CHARNAME>, we must overcome the obstacles this creature puts in our way if we are to achieve it.~
@67   = ~Finally, the creature shows some emotion. The mere mention of elves nearly drove it insane.~
@68   = ~Fanatics... I sense something bad is about to happen here, <CHARNAME>...~
@69   = ~The time of judgment has come, Gaal! You will pay with blood for those innocent lives lost because of you!~
@70   = ~It appears the god is taking on the form of a beast. We must be careful, beholders are not creatures to be taken lightly.~
@71   = ~Almost every century?! Damn it...~
@72   = ~The artifact does not belong to us. <CHARNAME> is doing the right thing, at least you should give them the benefit of the doubt.~
@73   = ~This guy is a bore, <CHARNAME>. I certainly hope our efforts will be worth it.~
@74   = ~If there's one thing I'd like to avoid, it's killing in the name of this idiot, <CHARNAME>. I hope you can find the wisdom to do the right thing.~
@75   = ~Clearly, this is a Guild of Nitwits, <CHARNAME>. Kill for this... this red jerk? (sigh) I suppose I could handle it, if necessary.~
@76   = ~<CHARNAME>, I hope we don't have to resort to murder this time. I believe we can be a bit more... diplomatic, don't you think?~
@77   = ~He's quite charismatic for a thief. Let's see what he has to say...~
@78   = ~Finally, someone worth killing. You might be surprised to hear me say this, but I hope we're assigned the task of killing that bastard.~
@79   = ~This guy is as charismatic as Renal. However, I can't help but think we might be getting swindled...~
@80   = ~I think the cemetery creature comes into play here, <CHARNAME>... It's surely giving these thieves a run for their money.~
@81   = ~It all points to a final showdown with the creature, doesn't it? I can't wait to stir up some trouble among the undead.~
@82   = ~And it all culminated in the tragedy of the Promenade and the death of dozens of innocent people. I must say, it was a shame you couldn't solve this earlier, Aran.~

@20000   = ~Hark, <CHARNAME>, just because you have your own quest doesn't mean you can't help others, especially a child who has lost his mother...~
@20001	 = ~We need to be careful. These are the slums, so trusting a stranger is potentially dangerous. Still, if this fool tries anything, my quarterstaff will make him see stars.~
@20002	 = ~Finally... we will meet the leader of the Shadow Thieves. He better make our efforts worth it...~
@20003	 = ~Even I can understand that Faldorn is an affront to nature. Using animals for revenge killings is a cowardly and dirty tactic. Jaheira, I hope you can kick her butt.~

@20007	 = ~Couldn't have said it better myself, Dusk.~
@20008	 = ~What's this? Stick man trying to give me warnings? You can try to stop me, stick man... just try...~
@20009	 = ~We'll see, mage... we'll see...~
@20010	 = ~An imposing creature... They say ancient dragons are among the most powerful creatures in the Realms... I think it's best we postpone this fight... I think...~
@20011	 = ~Your day of reckoning has come, dragon! Prepare to feel our wrath!!!~
@20012	 = ~Excavating beasts? I'm thinking they might be Umber Hulks... Or... Giant Shrews.~
@20013	 = ~Giant Shrews? Boo shudders at the very thought.~
@20014	 = ~Shrews? You have quite the imagination, Dusk.~
@20015	 = ~*clears throat* I think I'll go with the theory of Umber Hulks...~
@20016	 = ~It's possible, though I don't see why he would do something like that. Provoking an open war against the cities is not the way to preserve balance.~
@20017	 = ~I've met some druids. While they can be strange, I don't see any reason for them to start a senseless war. But again, it's very likely a druid.~
@20018	 = ~Maybe, but wait until I continue my story.~
@20019	 = ~I'm not sure if we can trust the djinn, <CHARNAME>. Nothing guarantees that they will keep their word.~


@20020	 = ~But what do I hear? A little mortal doubting the words of the great Khan Zahraa. I should send you to another plane for such insolence... but I'll tell you what: if you bring me what I ask for, I'll give you an artifact worthy of someone of your... class.~
@20021	 = ~We don't act for the reward, creature. We do it to help the people you oppress. If you don't keep your promise to leave, you can be sure you'll face us...~
@20022	 = ~*laugh* How amusing you humans are!~
@20023	 = ~I suppose I owe you an apology, genie. After all, you've kept your word.~
@20024	 = ~Ah, but if it isn't the mistrustful mortal. Indeed, wanderer, don't think I've forgotten about you. This sash is very strange and I sense that you may find it more useful than I.~
@20025	 = ~I agree, Dusk. Typical trickery, coming from the Cowled Wizards...~
@20026	 = ~Boo asks, why did you look at Minsc when you said "thick-headed"~
@20027	 = ~*coughs* Oh, no, my dear Minsc. I wasn't insinuating anything. I just remembered... uh... a friend, named... Munsc. Yes, that's it.~
@20028	 = ~Munsc? What a great name! He must be a good friend of yours, Dusk.~
@20029	 = ~One of the best.~
@20030	 = ~Even in the darkness you seek to help others, rivvil. You should know that such actions in the Underdark will lead you to a painful death.~
@20031	 = ~If you were the one in trouble, Viconia, I wouldn't hesitate to help you. That's what companions are for.~
@20032	 = ~Hmm... are you trying to seduce me, abbil? Oh, Dusk, protect me, I'm a damsel in distress!~
@20033	 = ~Ha! Is that how you woo your females? I warn you, you'll need much more than sweet words to satisfy me, my dear abbil.~
@20034	 = ~*sigh* Why did I even speak?~
@20035	 = ~Y-you don't look that bad, Dusk. Don't make that face. After all, that's what you would look like if you were born an elf. A dark-skinned one.~
@20036	 = ~Yeah, well... you haven't changed much either. Just your skin tone has darkened, but I can still clearly see that you're Aerie.~
@20037	 = ~I can even see that you have a resemblance to Viconia, heh.~
@20038	 = ~I heard that, rivvil. Your jokes may cost you dearly.~
@20039	 = ~This time I agree with Viconia. Dusk, retract your words.~
@20040	 = ~Very well, very well. Stop looking at me like that. *sigh* I think I talk too much lately...~
@20041	 = ~Condemnation? <CHARNAME>, we cannot allow harm to come to Viconia. Once again she is judged solely by her race!~
@20042   = ~Calm down, abbil. I can take care of myself.~

@20043   = ~Now calm down, Viconia. I'm sure <CHARNAME> was joking. He has a pretty strange sense of humor...~ ~Now calm down, Viconia. I'm sure <CHARNAME> was joking. She has a pretty strange sense of humor...~
@83   = ~This guy is so unpleasant, <CHARNAME>. However, it's better if you keep asking him about it. I have a feeling there's more going on here than meets the eye.~
@84   = ~I'm boiling with anger, <CHARNAME>! Let's do our best to free these slaves and make the culprits pay. Count me in.~
@85   = ~Slavery is a very profitable business. The price we pay for freedom isn't visible, but it costs a lot. Putting an end to these disgusting slavers is the best thing we can do.~
@86   = ~We've done something good here, <CHARNAME>. I'm sure Hendak will do his best to improve the quality of life for those who were slaves.~
@87   = ~Young lady, the fact that you barely escaped, doesn't that tell you something? Aegisfield did the right thing by giving us your name.~
@88   = ~So you admit it... Scum. You will pay for what you've done...~
@89   = ~You need to be careful, lieutenant. The bastard had set up a bunch of deadly traps, there might still be some left. Oh, and if I were you, I'd wear a mask... The stench there is... unbearable.~
@90   = ~I have no complaints about doing this quest, however, this elven wizard seems a bit unstable... I would recommend being careful, whether we succeed or not.~
@91   = ~It's been a strange adventure, <CHARNAME>, but it's always good to take on slavers. I hope Raelis doesn't have any problems opening that portal...~
@92   = ~Are you crazy, wizard? At no point did they mention that we had permission to use your filthy spells willy-nilly. Don't think I'll sit idly by if you intend to harm innocents with your magic!~
@93   = ~I'm no one to judge other people's mistakes. Especially those who try to redeem themselves despite not having a place in the world... I hope we're doing the right thing, <CHARNAME>.~
@94   = ~They're asking you to accept a deal without even knowing the details beforehand? *sigh*... typical cowardly mage behavior...~
@95   = ~Their ranger is missing? It's strange indeed... were there any tracks in her cabin? Perhaps she just went hunting?~
@96   = ~I don't think they're responsible for this mystery, <CHARNAME>. Hunting them down without them having done anything wrong would be a mistake. I think it's better if we keep investigating.~
@97   = ~It's odd... but I feel a strange nostalgia just looking at them... They're beautiful creatures. You did the right thing by setting them free, <CHARNAME>. They belong in the forest. And to freedom.~
@98   = ~I'm more and more convinced, my friend, that your divine lineage isn't such a well-kept secret...~
@99   = ~The girl isn't lacking in courage, <CHARNAME>. I think she'd be a good addition to the party. However, I also understand if you decide not to risk her neck on this venture.~


@103  = ~Clearly, this guy is not all there.~
@104  = ~That makes sense... Could it be a druid?~


@107  = ~*whisper* Something's not right... Keep your guard up, just in case...~
@108  = ~Of the three words this guy says, four are lies. However, <CHARNAME>, (despite the risk of being betrayed by this toad again) I think we should hear him out.~
@109  = ~Damn it, Saemon...~
@110  = ~The bastard has fooled us again...~
@111  = ~These arcane places... they reek of corruption...~
@112  = ~It's strange, I don't sense any magical energy in this guy. However, it's clear that he's not in his right mind. Poor guy...~

@114  = ~It's clear that he won't let your friend go just like that, <CHARNAME>. I think we should prepare for an inevitable fight...~

@116  = ~Certainly, this fish-man is very stubborn. He reminds me of someone...~
@117  = ~This civilization is incredible. It seems to be extremely ancient. I don't think many men have stepped on these... sticky tiles.~
@118  = ~It doesn't surprise me. <CHARNAME>, your Bhaal lineage surely has something to do with it.~
@119  = ~*whisper* Maybe you can convince him with some perspicacity, <CHARNAME>. If you don't understand me, send me to talk to him directly. I think the key is in the word "chest"...~
@120  = ~I've read about the svirfneblin. In general, they are benevolent creatures. If they need our help, we should not hesitate, <CHARNAME>. Maybe we can even do some good in this place.~
@121  = ~I am still amazed. This dragoness is extremely beautiful. A marvelous creature.~
@122  = ~Damn... I never thought that one day I would become a... drow...~
@123  = ~Lo and behold! So there are problems in paradise, huh?~


@126  = ~I would have expected a warmer welcome from the surface elves... although I can understand their high level of distrust.~
@127  = ~We must hurry, <CHARNAME>! The city of the elves is in danger. For the memory of Celine, I will protect their people!~

