@129  = ~So, <CHARNAME>... who was that mage who attacked you in the Promenade?~
@130  = ~His name is Irenicus. At least, that's what we were able to find out through some dryads he had captive in his dungeon. And his interest in my lineage.~ //t1.1
@131  = ~His name is not important, Dusk. What's important is that we find him and get answers as to why he was interested in my lineage.~ //t1.2
@132  = ~I don't think this is a good time to talk, Dusk. Maybe later.~ //t.0

//t.0 

@144  = ~Very well, very well. I won't bother you for now. But just know that whatever I don't know, I'll find out on my own, <CHARNAME>.~

//t1.1
@133  = ~Irenicus, huh? His face was strange... like there was no life in his eyes. The way he tore through those thieves and mages... it makes me shiver just thinking about it.~
// Sigue en 223 porque el texto era muy largo. Se dividió (GLOBAL 8)
@134  = ~However, you mentioned dryads and dungeons... I would like to know more about it, if you don't mind, of course.~

@135  = ~After my travels in the north and my adventures in Baldur's Gate, I was kidnapped, I still don't know by whom. That's when we woke up in some kind of dungeon. We owe our escape to Imoen's resourcefulness, and on the way we came across these dryads.~ //t1.11
@136  = ~The bastard had us in a dungeon and we came across some magical harlots. That's the short version, Dusk. We should probably continue on our journey.~ //t.0

//t1.11
@137  = ~I've had the misfortune of crossing paths with some dungeons and the luck of crossing paths with some dryads. Something tells me that if I stay by your side long enough, I'll do the same again. Not all dungeons are terrible places... and certainly, dryads are special creatures. Just mentioning them brings several memories to mind...~
@138  = ~But those are stories for another time, my friend.~
@139  = ~For now, the only question I have is about your lineage... what do you mean? Don't tell me you're related to some pompous noble. You don't look the part.~

@140  = ~It's none of your business, lad. We have more important things to do now.~ //t.0
@141  = ~Perhaps it's too soon to talk about it, Dusk. But I promise we will in the future, yes?~ //t1.12

//t1.12
@142  = ~Agreed, <CHARNAME>. I'll take you at your word. I promise to do the same on my end. For now, let me just say... it's a pleasure traveling with you.~

//opcion t1.2
//t1.2

@143  = ~Strange response. I think names are important... it's how we identify ourselves... but I respect your words.~
