@174  = ~I think I can talk to you about the Giant's Plain and the Shadow Forest now, <CHARNAME>. About my fight against the orcs and mountain trolls, would you like to hear?~

// + t3.1 ir a @178
@175  = ~Well, Dusk. I'm eager to hear your story.~

// + t3.0 ir a @177
@176  = ~To be honest, I'd prefer if you give me the short version, Dusk. Your narrations are not entertaining at all.~ 

// = t3.0
@177  = ~A… short version? Well, I guess I should tell you that my entire Cormyr detachment was wiped out by a skirmish with orcs and trolls… and I was nearly killed… had it not been for an elven archer named Celine. Short enough for you? Damn it, <CHARNAME>…~

@178  = ~After our landing in Ilipur, I led my detachment south. The plan was to cross the Giant Plain and head towards the lands of Tethyr. For a few nights, we had no problems… but…~
@179  = ~It was near the Esmel River's mouth… we were attacked by an orc army, which had some trolls among their ranks.~
@180  = ~My detachment consisted of no more than twenty men, brave warriors of Cormyr, trained by the Knights of the Order of the Purple Dragon…~
@181  = ~But they outnumbered us… perhaps tripled our numbers. And that was only on the first night of a succession of attacks.~
@182  = ~With courage we fought and were able to defeat the first wave. We lost about five soldiers. That was when the second wave arrived.~
@183  = ~This time we had to retreat. After a few days, our resources were already scarce, as we used many fire arrows and acid darts to bring down the mountain trolls.~
@184  = ~By the time we ran out of ammunition, our number had dropped drastically. We lost ten more comrades… and then chaos took over.~
@185  = ~The few of us who survived fled eastward, towards a wooded area. Exhausted, at the entrance of the forest, we turned and fought once more.~
@186  = ~We were able to kill the orcs, but the trolls, after a few minutes, got back on their feet, completely regenerated from their wounds.~
@187  = ~I ordered my men to retreat… I think the trolls got many of them…~


@188  = ~I kept fighting with my bastard sword, taking the battle into the darkness of the forest.~
@189  = ~Rage filled my chest. I felt that my failure fueled my hatred towards those horrible creatures, because I could no longer fulfill my mission of bringing peace to the southern nations... And I kept fighting...~
