@3029  = ~Verily, <CHARNAME>! You had Boo rolling on the floor laughing.~
@3030  = ~Gosh, <CHARNAME>. *giggles* That was really funny.~
@3031  = ~This is a waste of time, <CHARNAME>. I hope your little trick works.~
@3032  = ~Darn it... He runs like a gazelle... Come on, <CHARNAME>. Let's try it again.~
@3033  = ~Hmm... I don't know, <CHARNAME>. That might offend the dwarves, don't you think?~
@3034  = ~Ha! What are ye worried about, scrawny? <CHARNAME>'s joke was really good. In fact, I told it at my aunt's funeral. It was a hit.~
@3035  = ~Great job, <CHARNAME>! You were wonderful.~
@3036  = ~Oh, <CHARNAME>. I don't think that was a good idea.~
@3037  = ~(I don't think that's how the saying goes, <CHARNAME>)~



@3038  = ~Verily, Mathyus, it is <CHARNAME> who deserves all the credit. He knew how to handle the situation, despite Michelson's demands.~ ~Verily, Mathyus, it is <CHARNAME> who deserves all the credit. She knew how to handle the situation, despite Michelson's demands.~
@3039  = ~The little one didn't make it easy for us, Mathyus. But fortunately, we succeeded.~
@3040  = ~Finally! My precious armor returns to me... thank you, friends. Thank you too, <CHARNAME>.~

@3041  = ~I'm glad I could be of help.~
@3042  = ~*ahem* Let's just say nothing in this life is free, gentlemen. I hope this effort is worth at least some reward.~
@3043  = ~No problem... just try not to lose sight of the tadpole again, Mathyus, yes?~
@3044  = ~Ermm... a small detail I forgot to mention. Apologies.~
@3045  = ~(Hmmm... I'm not sure that's how the saying goes)~
@3046  = ~Bald'? Well, Minsc doesn't see the problem with that, do you, Boo?~
@3047  = ~TI appreciate it, my friend.~
@3048  = ~A quest? Dusk, what is he referring to?~
@3049  = ~Ah, <CHARNAME>. Don't worry... in due time, you'll know. It's nothing we can't handle.~

@3050  = ~Erhm... very well, Mathyus. Michelson! I entrust my weapon to you. I trust you all.~
@3051  = ~Hark... the power it radiates... it's incredible...~

@3052  = ~Very well... here you go... (Darn it, I feel naked)~
@3053  = ~It's much heavier... but its craftsmanship is magnificent...~
@3054  = ~Gathering the Duke's set hasn't been easy, Mathyus and Michelson...~
@3055  = ~Hark... the effort has finally paid off.~
@3056  = ~What?! Darn it, <CHARNAME>, what have you done with my staff? (that's what I get for trusting you with my things). We better find it and come back. The Royal Avenger is something worth having, believe me.~
@3057  = ~Thanks for helping me retrieve it, <CHARNAME>. That way, we both avoid the awkward moment where I kick your butt for losing it in the first place. *smiles*~
@3058  = ~The Shilmist staff has been with me from the beginning... but the Royal Avenger will serve us better for our purpose... So yes... I accept the change.~
@3059  = ~*sigh* A deal is a deal, my little friend. Here's my precious Shilmist staff.~

@3060  = ~Demoli?! What the heck are you doing here?~
@3061  = ~Dusk, do you know this mutt?~
@3062  = ~But what a cute little doggie! Do you know him, Dusk? What's his name?~
@3063  = ~Great, a stray dog... I guess we're not adopting him, huh? This isn't an animal shelter, mate.~
@3064  = ~<CHARNAME>, this is Demolisher. He's not just any dog, as he appears. He's Mathyus' animal companion.~
@3065  = ~Demolisher? He doesn't seem that demolishing to me.~
@3066  = ~He belongs to Mathyus? I'm not surprised.~
@3067  = ~What brings you here, Demoli? Let me see this note...~
@3068  = ~"Dear Dusk, we have found a lead on the attacks on your detachment. It's best you come as soon as possible. 
Sincerely, 
Mathyus, the powerful guardian elf of Shilmista."~
@3069  = ~<CHARNAME>, we should head to the Athkatla's Docks and see Mathyus right away.~
@3070  = ~Does it have to be immediate, Dusk? We have things to take care of.~
@3071  = ~What's happening, Dusk? I hope it's nothing serious.~
@3072  = ~Very well, we'll go right away.~
@3073  = ~Let's do what we need to do, <CHARNAME>, and then come with me. I'll need your help, most likely.~
@3074  = ~I'm not sure, my friend. But we'll find out as soon as we get there.~
@3075  = ~Gratitude, <CHARNAME>.~
@3076  = ~Demolisher, run and tell your master to wait for us, yes?~
@3077  = ~But, what the-...?~

// MISION 2

@3078  = ~Mathyus, have you finally been able to find them?~
@3079  = ~Excellent, Mathyus... excellent...~
@3080  = ~Dusk, I think it's time you told us what all this is about.~
@3081  = ~This is related to your old soldier brotherhood, isn't it?~
@3082  = ~<CHARNAME>, I'm sorry I kept you in the dark about this matter.~
@3083  = ~When we arrived in these lands from the north, my detachment and I were attacked by waves of orcs and hill trolls. I must have mentioned this to you, haven't I?~
@3084  = ~All... all of my companions were slain in battle by these horrid creatures...~
@3085  = ~Once my wounds were healed in Shilmista, I returned to search for their bodies and give them a proper burial.~
@3086  = ~While I was finding what... what remains I could, I couldn't help but wonder...~
@3087  = ~What if these attacks weren't random? What if they were orchestrated by a dark force that I cannot glimpse?~
@3088  = ~Do you really think orcs are capable of such plans, Dusk? You give them too much credit in my opinion.~
@3089  = ~Do you think this could have been originated by someone beyond the orcs?~

@3090  = ~If you had asked me back then, I wouldn't have been so sure. But now...~
@3091  = ~I trained to become a Wizard Slayer after losing my detachment and some... events that I will tell you about in the future. During that training, I had a vision in which I could glimpse a shield with the emblem of the Purple Dragon. It was broken... shattered by a fierce battle.~
@3092  = ~That image stayed in my mind, until I could come here and tell Mathyus about it.~
@3093  = ~I'm sure it's them, <CHARNAME>!~
@3094  = ~I saw it clearly, a long time ago, in my mind... humanoids carrying Cormyr artifacts, as if it were a trophy.~
@3095  = ~It hasn't been long since I entrusted this search to Mathyus... that means they are relatively close to Athkatla, <CHARNAME>.~
@3096  = ~What we have to do is clear: we must hunt down these creatures. I will give justice to my fallen comrades.~
@3097  = ~Mathyus, we've talked about it already. Now, as you promised me... give me the location of this tribe.~

@3099  = ~hank you, Mathyus... really.~
@3100  = ~Don't worry, friend. <CHARNAME> travels with me... and I count on their advice in difficult times.~
@3101  = ~So be it, Mathyus. Rest assured we'll come back... victorious.~


@3102  = ~Finally... we've found them! The purple shield... <CHARNAME>, he was right... they have it...~
@3103  = ~<CHARNAME>, you're right. Listen to me, creature... Your evil ends here. For Cormyr, I condemn you to death!~
@3104  = ~Good, scrawny. I like yer determination. Leave that giant to me, will ye? My axe thirsts for blood... Ha!~
@3105  = ~I don't agree with this, Dusk... but I suppose if we don't destroy them now, these humanoids could do harm to innocents.~
@3106  = ~Listen? They're orcs! The only thing they should listen to is the metallic sound of my sword as it pierces their dark hearts...~
@3107  = ~You didn't strike me as the type of man to give in to rage so easily, Dusk. Please, listen to me... and listen to them.~
@3108  = ~You're right, Dusk... Evil will always be evil... Let's attack!~
@3109  = ~(Damn...) So be it, <CHARNAME>... I'll follow your advice. Creature! My friend has convinced me to listen to you... so... you have our attention.~
@3110  = ~I see, these creatures were part of the army seeking to invade Amn... I believe that's another reason to annihilate them, <CHARNAME>.~
@3111  = ~The noble knights have been fighting creatures like these for months, <CHARNAME>. However, these ones don't seem to have the bloodlust of the ogre's minions.~
@3112  = ~Ah... Sothillis... the ogre mage who has created his own empire... He's managed to gather a considerable number of humanoids who only seek to take the land of men here in Amn. Why should I think you're any different from them?~
@3113  = ~What you're saying sounds very nice... but there's something that doesn't add up in your story...~
@3114  = ~I'm referring to the broken shield you carry with you. It belongs to the Order of the Purple Dragons of Cormyr! I demand an answer, now!~
@3115  = ~Do you expect me to believe that, Falon? Am I supposed to believe that the shield just appeared out of nowhere in your camp?~
@3116  = ~*sigh* I hate to admit it... but the ettin is right... I need advice...~

@3117  = ~<CHARNAME>, Forgive me to put the weight of the final decision on you... but my heart doesn't allow my mind to decide clearly on the matter. What do you think about it?~
@3118  = ~Argh! Minsc gets confused in these situations. However, Boo thinks that not everything should end in combat, good Dusk.~
@3119  = ~W-well... I think this tribe isn't evil, Dusk. I-think you should give them a chance... Even, help them.~
@3120  = ~Sometimes it's wise to share the responsibility of a decision, young Dusk. I think you're doing the right thing by trusting the judgment of your companions.~
@3121  = ~Well, if you ask me, Dusk... I would try to avoid conflict if possible. But I don't reject a brawl either.~
@3122  = ~I've faced many humanoids, Dusk. And, certainly, none have been like this tribe. I find it hard to believe that they orchestrated an attack against a Cormyr detachment.~
@3123  = ~They don't seem like opponents worthy of our attention... However, I think they shouldn't be free. A good judge in Athkatla would have already sentenced them to the stake.~
@3124  = ~Firsthand, I have bad experience dealing with humanoids... But, Dusk... these creatures don't seem violent.~
@3125  = ~Dusk, I understand that you want to avenge your comrades in arms... but keep in mind, that this tribe may not be responsible for such attack.~
@3126  = ~Nature indicates the innate violence in many humanoids, Dusk. But I can't see that in this tribe. It may be that, in the end, they were not responsible for such attack.~
@3127  = ~I know very well what it's like to be judged by a corrupt clan, Dusk. I don't want to believe that ours fits into that classification. Don't let hate cloud your judgment, my friend.~
@3128  = ~Abbil, I know very well what it's like to be judged only by your race. Judged by the vile rivvil... And I believe, Dusk, that you're not like the rest of the rivvil.~
@3129  = ~Well, if you ask me (something you haven't done yet, but you can't expect less from a party of primates), I'd say we fry them with magic. The humanoids of Sothillis don't deserve to live in the world of men.~
@3130  = ~Hmpf... Did ye say something, scrawny? Just say the magic word and Korgan will take care of this pathetic band of orcs. My axe also longs for it.~

@3131  = ~This reminds me of a situation my uncle Gerhardt experienced. The poor gnome had been accused of stealing an entire farm of pheasants. Rumors suggested that my uncle planned to build an army of pheasants and raid different turnip farms throughout Faerûn. After a few days, a detachment of guards came to my house. Fortunately, they were able to refute the vile rumors about Gerhardt. As retaliation, he planned to build an army of ferrets in the following months to make the rumors come true. I still don't know what came of that plan. But it certainly had its potential.~
@3132  = ~Well, well, the white canary is in some kind of discrepancy with its desires. I would say: don't think too much. Dance a bit and let your feet decide your fate (and theirs too).~
@3133  = ~Dusk, I don't think these humanoids are responsible for your attack...~
@3134  = ~Dusk, I think these humanoids deserve to die for what they are: members of the Sothillis Empire.~
@3135  = ~Dusk, I think we should investigate this matter further. Especially about the broken shield of Cormyr.~
@3136  = ~Dusk, I think we are being set up. We should attack before it's too late.~
@3137  = ~You may be right... but I feel we should investigate more...~
@3138  = ~The matter of the shield, Falon... it has me puzzled... Tell me, where do they come from?~
@3139  = ~I see... now... about the shield...~
@3140  = ~Negative energy? Maybe the shield... after all... was planted.~
@3141  = ~Never mind, Falon. Through <CHARNAME>'s help, we have been able to find out quite a bit about the matter.~
@3142  = ~By the way, you can stop calling me 'human'. My name is Ardusk Aldant. You can call me Dusk.~
@3143  = ~I'd like to ask you one last favor.~
@3144  = ~The shield of Cormyr... beyond being broken, it belongs to my people. I'd like you to give it to me.~
@3145  = ~I appreciate it... is there anything I can do for you? Consider it as an apology for my somewhat... aggressive introduction to you.~
@3146  = ~The fact that you are deserters from Sothillis would complicate matters for you, right? I understand...~
@3147  = ~I think we can solve that problem. If I intervene for you in the Noble Order of the Radiant Heart, perhaps we can do something about it.~
@3148  = ~You just keep a low profile and wait for me here. <CHARNAME>, we should go to the Noble Order of the Radiant Heart to talk to Sir Ryan Trawl. I'm sure he can help us.~
@3149  = ~For Cormyr, who the hell are you?~

@3150  = ~What...? Mage, explain yourself! Who are you... and how do you know me?~
@3151  = ~Oh... darn... <CHARNAME>... I think this mage... is the one who planted the shield in the tribe of these humanoids...~
@3152  = ~No... I...~
@3153  = ~Bastard... why? Why did you do it? Why did you want me to massacre these innocents...?~
@3154  = ~You're beating around the bush, mage. I demand an explanation!~
@3155  = ~Master? What the hell are you talking about?~
@3156  = ~Damned...~
@3157  = ~You bastard... If you go near them, I...~
@3158  = ~*whisper* What...?~
@3159  = ~...~
@3160  = ~<CHARNAME>... I'm sorry...~
@3161  = ~And you're right, Dusk. Your business has led a clan of psychopaths to discover my identity.~
@3162  = ~Don't worry, Dusk. It's not like it's such a well-kept secret at this point.~
@3163  = ~I'll try to make it up to you... with my life if possible...~
@3164  = ~However... you can't understand the hatred that fills my heart...~
@3165  = ~I feel... I feel a rage that I can barely contain...~
@3166  = ~Not only have I killed the wrong creatures... but I've exposed those closest to me...~
@3167  = ~I think... I think the path I've been trying to follow so far hasn't worked... many times... many times I tried to act right... believing... believing that it would always lead to a good outcome...~
@3168  = ~But I keep making the wrong decisions... over and over again... and I always put those around me in danger...~
@3169  = ~That's over, <CHARNAME>... I feel like I've been holding back my entire life... and the path of violence is the one I've chosen, from the start.~
@3170  = ~So... I think that's the answer... The path I choose now must be the right one, isn't it?~
@3171  = ~<CHARNAME>... you've opened my eyes... and for that, I thank you.~
@3172  = ~You have my loyalty until the end of my days. I'll follow you until one of us is reached by the arms of death.~
@3173  = ~Let's go... we've had enough with what happened today... Let's go to Mathyus and explain what has happened here. Maybe they'll know what to do with this damn orb...~


@3174  = ~Sir Ryan Trawl, on behalf of Cormyr, it is a pleasure to greet you.~
@3175  = ~With our party, we have been able to locate several renegade humanoids from the Sothillis empire. Their chieftain seeks to live in peace, away from the war that his former boss has provoked.~
@3176  = ~Well... after talking with them, I promised to find them a home here in Amn. I know I am asking for a lot, but I believe I have helped the city in the past as much as I could. All I seek is an opportunity...~
@3177  = ~They are not a violent tribe, not even numerous, my lord. If they were under the protection of the Order, I believe they would be useful in the war being waged against the Sothillis empire.~
@3178  = ~I think they could provide vital information about the ogre army, my lord. They may even fight on your side if asked to do so. As long as they are promised a home here in Amn.~
@3179  = ~Gratitude, Sir Ryan. I am sure that <CHARNAME> will be up to whatever you require of him.~ ~Gratitude, Sir Ryan. I am sure that <CHARNAME> will be up to whatever you require of her.~
@3180  = ~Sir Ryan, now that the matter of the fallen paladins has been resolved...~
@3181  = ~Fantastic news! <CHARNAME>, let's go back to the Windspear Hills and give the good news to Falon and his tribe.~
@3182  = ~Thank you, Ziben. I accept, honored...~
@3183  = ~Come on, <CHARNAME>. I think it's time to update Mathyus on the mission's status.~
@3184  = ~Oh... darn... <CHARNAME>... I think this wizard... is the one who planted the shield in Falon's tribe...~
@3185  = ~Bastard... You planted that shield on innocent humanoids and you call me pathetic for doing the right thing?~
@3186  = ~But... but at least I didn't make the mistake of attacking Falon and his tribe.~
@3187  = ~I offer my gratitude to you, <CHARNAME>. You saved me from making an unforgivable mistake.~
@3188  = ~This may have been what they call a crossroads in life... I believe that what separates us from evil, many times, is a simple decision.~
@3189  = ~You have my loyalty, until the end of my days, <CHARNAME>. I will follow you, knowing that there is a halo at the end of the road.~
@3190  = ~For now, let's go back to Mathyus. Maybe my friends know something about this cursed orb...~
@3191  = ~Falon! Good news: <CHARNAME> and I have convinced Sir Ryan Trawl to get you and your tribe a home in the Noble Order of the Radiant Heart. I will show you and your tribe how to get there...~
@3192  = ~Likewise, I must say... I think you will need to provide information about Sothillis to the paladins. I don't think there are any precedents for them to welcome humanoids so willingly into their quarters.~
@3193  = ~I doubt the knights are tyrants. They will not be forced to do anything they do not want to do, as they have given me their word. Otherwise, do not hesitate to come to me...~


@3194  = ~I'm sure our paths will cross again someday, friends. In the meantime, I'll visit you in the Temple District when I can.~
@3195  = ~We found the tribe of humanoids, Mathyus. The information provided by Demolisher was accurate.~
@3196  = ~However, they weren't responsible for the attack on my detachment...~
@3197  = ~That's right... as we speak, their blood feeds the soil of Windspear Hills.~
@3198  = ~They were deserters from the Sothillis Empire. They deserved their final fate, Mathyus.~
@3199  = ~Does that reason seem sufficient to you?~
@3200  = ~So, they died because they were humanoids, Mathyus. Don't overthink it.~
@3201  = ~When we finished off the humanoids, a mysterious mage appeared.~
@3202  = ~He called himself Sornhil. He was responsible for planting the Cormyrean shield in the humanoid camp.~
@3203  = ~Although I knew it once I finished them off.~
@3204  = ~After a brief... conversation, he gave me this orb.~
@3205  = ~I understand... and what do I have to do to unleash its power?~
@3206  = ~I see... if you manage to remove that evil, the orb's powers would be diminished, is that correct?~
@3207  = ~Ultimately, no one is sure what might happen if I use it...~


@3208  = ~But... if Sornhil and his Order are what I think they are... I can't afford to waste such power.~
@3209  = ~I'm going to use it, Mathyus. I need to know how to activate it.~
@3210  = ~Silence, both of you! I've made my decision and there's no turning back. Mathyus, I'll ask you only once. How do you activate the orb?~
@3211  = ~Very well. Here it is...~
@3212  = ~Hello? Dusk! Stop fooling around and talk to me.~
@3213  = ~Dusk? Mathyus, what's going on? The orb has started to glow.~
@3214  = ~I've seen what you offer me... and I accept it. Now... give me your power!~
@3215  = ~It's over...~
@3216  = ~What are you looking at?~
@3217  = ~Dusk? By Candlekeep, you look vastly different.~
@3218  = ~Dusk, are you well? You've... changed.~
@3219  = ~I've never felt so alive...~
@3220  = ~Mathyus... you still have a mission to find the true culprits behind the attack on my detachment, understood?~
@3221  = ~And this time... I won't tolerate any failures. Do you understand me?~
@3222  = ~Excellent...~
@3223  = ~<CHARNAME>, we better continue with our own affairs... When the time comes, I'll request your services to hunt some orcs.~
@3224  = ~Verily, I didn't expect you to be so demanding. So be it.~
@3225  = ~Who do you think you are, mate? I'll do as I please when it pleases me.~
@3226  = ~That's what I like to hear...~
@3227  = ~Very well, <CHARNAME>... keep that killer rage... I'm sure it will be useful to us in the not too distant future...~
@3228  = ~That's right... The tribe turned out to be deserters from the Sothillis Empire. They were fleeing south when we found them.~

@3230  = ~After a brief conversation, and through the intervention of <CHARNAME>, I decided they would be safer in Athkatla.~
@3231  = ~I went to the Noble Order of the Radiant Heart and Sir Ryan Trawl gave them a home in their barracks.~
@3232  = ~My destiny? I don't understand, what do you mean?~
@3233  = ~Well... I thought I could finally avenge my fallen comrades, Mathyus. However, it only ended in a search that left us with more questions than answers.~
@3234  = ~When we gave the humanoids a new home, a mysterious mage appeared.~
@3235  = ~He called himself Sornhil. He was responsible for planting the Cormyrian shield in Falon's camp.~
@3236  = ~I must use it, Mathyus... The Order to which Sornhil belongs... I must find out more about them. Using the orb, despite the danger it entails, is the only option. But...~
@3237  = ~I'm listening, <CHARNAME>. And although I appreciate your advice... I have doubts in my heart. I believe... I believe that...~

@3238  = ~Actually, purification seems to be a viable option. Michelson is a powerful being, capable of achieving such a thing, isn't he, Mathyus?~
@3239  = ~Michelson... you did it...~
@3240  = ~Thank you, my friend. Mathyus, I think I'm ready to use it.~
@3241  = ~Very well. Here it is... the purified orb...~
@3242  = ~Thank you... for granting me that vision...~
@3243  = ~I appreciate the attention, but there are more important things to attend to, don't you think?~
@3244  = ~The orb has vanished, Mathyus. I think it has taken the form of this emerald sword that Michelson has pointed out, which is now shining in my hands. I have seen your joyful movements, Demolisher. Thank you for caring.~
@3245  = ~Thank you, Mathyus. However, don't expose yourselves to danger. Sornhil and his Order of Mages seem to be something to deal with, but if we don't know more about them, that may not be a bad sign.~
@3246  = ~Revenge isn't always the answer. I know that now. <CHARNAME>, your aid has brought peace to my heart.~
@3247  = ~The dead don't desire revenge... I assume they would want their loved ones to live in peace and harmony. I speak for my fallen comrades in battle.~
@3248  = ~A wise decision, my friend. Let's go, we have matters to attend to.~
@3249  = ~Indeed, Dusk. You're completely changed. I think I like this version of you.~
@3250  = ~You're not going to start singing and dancing like that leprechaun, are you?~
@3251  = ~Very funny, <CHARNAME>. Come on, let's continue our journey.~
@3252  = ~Thank you, <CHARNAME>. Let's continue our journey.~
@3253  = ~Um... I appreciate it, Coco, but we're good. <CHARNAME> and I have some unfinished business to attend to... (Dang, it'll be hard to get rid of this tomato sauce).~

// Bellfame
@3254  = ~My little friend Michelson mentioned something about a disruption in time. I didn't think such a thing was possible.~
@3255  = ~The world of magic has the ability to alter time and space.~
@3256  = ~In my confrontation with Kartlzer's detachment, my druidic magic collided with the arcane magic of their sorcerer.~
@3257  = ~The ring that your fellowship now possesses was the conductor of that event... I don't think I can explain exactly what happened...~
@3258  = ~Well... whatever it was, your story in the Forest of Mir has not happened yet. That confuses me...~
@3259  = ~You don't need to understand everything around you, mortal. Sometimes, things... just happen.~
@3261  = ~It is true that I am a mortal, nymph... but my friends call me Dusk. You can call me that too.~

@3262  = ~Demolisher... I trust that your interruption is only due to news regarding the mission I assigned to your master.~
@3263  = ~Demoli! Glad to see you. I imagine Matyhus sent you. Any news?~
@3264  = ~"Dusk! We've finally located them. Or at least, him. The orc chieftain who organized the attack on your detachment is very close to Athkatla. It is necessary for you to return with <CHARNAME> to our hideout for more details. 
Sincerely, Mathyus. 
The powerful shilmist elf."~
@3265  = ~"The orc chieftain..."~
@3266  = ~After so long... I'll be able to avenge my fallen comrades...~
@3267  = ~That's good news, Dusk. I just hope Mathyus didn't screw it up this time. I'll accompany you.~
@3268  = ~We don't have time for this, Dusk. It will have to wait.~
@3269  = ~I hope the same, <CHARNAME>. But something tells me that this time... this time it's him...~
@3270  = ~Him? Who are you talking about?~
@3271  = ~Alabarza, the Mutilator. At least, that's what he boasted about shouting while we fought on the Eastern plains.~
@3272  = ~He's an half-orc who wielded two powerful axes. He managed to kill four of ours before I could find him on the battlefield.~
@3273  = ~One of his blows nearly decapitated me... luckily, my helmet prevented the fatal blow, although it was smashed in the process.~
@3274  = ~I managed to land a strike, but not fully, on his face. I think I succeeded in taking out one of his eyes... although I'm not certain. Some of his minions came to his aid at that moment.~
@3275  = ~He screamed loudly... and from the shadows came a giant troll, which made us retreat... That was the last time I heard of him.~
@3276  = ~<CHARNAME>, I'm sure Mathyus is referring to Alabarza. He must have survived his injuries... and surely has with him some emblem of Cormyr.~
@3277  = ~Demolisher, return to your master and tell him that we will go as soon as possible.~

@3278  = ~<CHARNAME>, if he's the enemy I think he is, he probably has a valuable treasure worth considering.~
@3279  = ~If that doesn't move you, perhaps the challenge of facing someone strong will. Alabarza is a foe to be feared.~
@3280  = ~"Treasure," you say? Now you're speaking my language. Tell me more.~
@3281  = ~More fearsome than me, Dusk? We'll see about that. Very well, you've convinced me. Tell me more.~
