// INTERACTIONS REST

@3381  = ~Not that I complain about having to kill a thief, <CHARNAME>. But I'd rather do it for my own reasons than out of necessity to deal with this scum...~

@3382  = ~<CHARNAME>, apparently we have found the tanner who escaped us in Athkatla. I think it's a good opportunity to do justice, don't you think?~
@3383  = ~Ha! Who would have thought? We have found the bastard flayer. It's a good opportunity to find out why he does what he does... although, if we have to kill him, there will be no complaints from me.~


//@3384  = ~Allí... en la oscuridad... ¿puedes verlo, <CHARNAME>?~

@3385  = ~It seems he is aware of our movements, <CHARNAME>. He even knows how much gold we have. Err... an uncomfortable fact if you ask me...~
@3386  = ~How does this woman know how much money we have? Damn it, <CHARNAME>. While supposedly offering the same as the Thieves for less money... This creature seems very... repugnant to me.~

@3387  = ~Listen to me, runt! <CHARNAME> has decided to return the artifact because he believed it was the right thing to do. The least you should do is thank him on your knees. Would that cost you anything? I could help you. You'll see that my sword is a good incentive...~

@3388  = ~You can't trust a djinn, <CHARNAME>. If you choose to pursue his prey, I suppose I can get behind that. But if it were up to me, I would exterminate them right here.~
